11:39.065 --> 11:41.033
<i>I could never</i>
<i>suspend my disbelief</i>

11:41.100 --> 11:44.837
<i>and fully immerse myself</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

11:44.904 --> 11:47.440
<i>I even got frustrated</i>
<i>when dream sequences</i>

11:47.506 --> 11:49.842
<i>would interrupt</i>
<i>the plot of a show,</i>

11:49.909 --> 11:51.477
<i>even though it was all</i>

11:51.544 --> 11:55.214
<i>completely made up</i>
<i>to begin with.</i>

11:55.281 --> 11:58.884
<i>And while everyone else</i>
<i>was going to Comic-Con,</i>

11:59.919 --> 12:03.222
<i>I started going</i>
<i>on court TV shows to</i>

12:03.289 --> 12:06.292
<i>fill the void</i>
<i>that was left behind.</i>

12:06.358 --> 12:08.260
-Judge Milian: Okay, John,
what is your last name?
-Wilson.

12:08.327 --> 12:10.096
-Judge Milian: Mr. Wilson,
how old are you?
-I'm 16.

12:10.162 --> 12:13.199
<i>This obsession lasted</i>
<i>well into adulthood,</i>

12:14.200 --> 12:16.368
<i>but it started to take a toll</i>

12:16.435 --> 12:18.871
<i>on a lot of my relationships.</i>

12:18.938 --> 12:21.507
Judge Acker:
Mr. Wilson, you're
a videographer?

12:21.574 --> 12:23.375
-I'm a freelance filmmaker.
-Judge Acker: Well,

12:23.442 --> 12:25.478
Mr. Freelance Filmmaker,
you're suing the defendant

12:25.544 --> 12:28.581
for $2,000 because,
according to your complaint,

12:28.647 --> 12:31.383
he hired you to do some
freelance filmmaking,

12:31.450 --> 12:33.052
-and then he didn't pay you!
-Yeah.

12:33.119 --> 12:36.188
<i>I won a few thousand</i>
<i>dollars over the years,</i>

12:36.255 --> 12:38.824
<i>but mostly all I did was</i>

12:38.891 --> 12:40.626
<i>just make enemies.</i>

12:40.693 --> 12:43.095
I think it's a victory for
freelancers everywhere.

12:43.162 --> 12:44.597
He was just trying to
take advantage of me.

12:44.663 --> 12:46.132
All he was trying to
do was get that money.

12:46.198 --> 12:48.300
I think that's
a moronic thing to say.

12:48.367 --> 12:50.870
<i>And I kind of wish</i>
<i>I could find value</i>

12:50.936 --> 12:54.373
<i>in the stuff</i>
<i>we make up in our heads.</i>

12:54.440 --> 12:58.110
<i>But, as you continue</i>
<i>to record your dreams,</i>

12:58.177 --> 13:01.580
<i>they just...</i>
<i>seem to get scarier.</i>

13:01.647 --> 13:04.250
<i>And instead of providing</i>
<i>you with nice thoughts</i>

13:04.316 --> 13:06.852
<i>that stick with you</i>
<i>throughout the day,</i>

13:06.919 --> 13:09.188
<i>every evening</i>
<i>begins to feel like</i>

13:09.255 --> 13:10.823
<i>an eight-hour nightmare</i>

13:10.890 --> 13:13.459
<i>that you just can't</i>

13:13.526 --> 13:15.561
<i>find a way to turn off.</i>

13:16.829 --> 13:20.533
<i>And one day, when you</i>
<i>left your dream journal</i>

13:20.599 --> 13:22.902
<i>on-- open on the table,</i>

13:22.968 --> 13:25.004
<i>your girlfriend walked by</i>

13:25.070 --> 13:29.275
<i>and read about a dream</i>
<i>that you had about an ex.</i>

13:29.341 --> 13:31.210
<i>She got really upset,</i>

13:31.277 --> 13:35.381
<i>and it kind of led</i>
<i>to a big argument.</i>

13:35.447 --> 13:40.152
<i>You told her it didn't matter</i>
<i>because it wasn't real,</i>

13:40.219 --> 13:43.923
<i>but she still felt otherwise.</i>

13:45.124 --> 13:48.160
<i>Maybe it's not a good idea</i>

13:48.227 --> 13:51.063
<i>to try to remember your dreams</i>

13:51.130 --> 13:54.667
<i>because once you bring</i>
<i>your subconscious</i>

13:54.733 --> 13:56.569
<i>into the real world,</i>

13:56.635 --> 14:01.140
<i>it could do real harm</i>
<i>to someone you love.</i>

14:01.207 --> 14:05.077
<i>And maybe you should just</i>
<i>go back to your comfort zone</i>

14:05.144 --> 14:08.614
<i>before you do</i>
<i>any more damage.</i>

14:10.182 --> 14:12.484
<i>Whenever you wanna relax,</i>

14:12.551 --> 14:15.254
<i>you like to turn on AM radio.</i>

14:15.321 --> 14:17.389
<i>Your favorite station</i>
